{
  "info": {
    "name": "AMAS Backend - End-to-End (Full Project)",
    "_postman_id": "d7d8d7c5-5c58-4cf9-9a2c-39b8bfe45a8a",
    "description": "End-to-end Postman collection based ONLY on FastAPI routes implemented in app/main.py and app/api.py.\n\nFastAPI routes included:\n- GET /\n- POST /agents/create\n- POST /agents/spawn\n- GET /agents\n- POST /shutdown/{agent_id}\n- POST /run\n- POST /ask\n- GET /tasks/{task_id}\n\nNotes from code behavior:\n- /ask enqueues the coordinator Celery task and long-polls until timeout_seconds.\n- /run enqueues and returns immediately.\n- /tasks/{task_id} polls Celery AsyncResult.\n- run_coordinator_task can use OpenAI or fall back to search results.\n\nEnvironment variables required:\n- base_url (example: http://localhost:8000)\n- agent_image (example: amas_agent_template:latest)\n\nNo authentication headers are required by this codebase.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET / (API root health)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Response has status ok', function () {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(j).to.have.property('status');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/",
            "description": "Defined in app/main.py. Returns {\"status\":\"ok\",\"service\":\"AMAS Backend\"}."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Ask (OpenAI-first + Search-only)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /ask (OpenAI-first; fallback to search if OpenAI fails)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or 202', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect([200, 202]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has task_id and result.answer', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('task_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('result');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.result).to.have.property('answer');",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (j.task_id) pm.environment.set('task_id', j.task_id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.test('202 contains task_id in detail', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('detail');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.detail).to.have.property('task_id');",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (j.detail && j.detail.task_id) pm.environment.set('task_id', j.detail.task_id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ask?timeout_seconds=180",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ask"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "timeout_seconds", "value": "180" }
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"goal\": \"Who is the current president of America?\",\n  \"requirements\": [],\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"use_openai\": true\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Implemented in app/api.py. Enqueues coordinator workflow and long-polls for completion.\n\nCoordinator task: app.celery_worker.run_coordinator_task\n- uses OpenAI when constraints.use_openai=true\n- falls back to a search-derived answer if OpenAI fails"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /ask (Search-only fallback / always works)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200 or 202', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect([200, 202]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  pm.test('Response has task_id and result.answer', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('task_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('result');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.result).to.have.property('answer');",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (j.task_id) pm.environment.set('task_id', j.task_id);",
                  "} else {",
                  "  pm.test('202 contains task_id in detail', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('detail');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.detail).to.have.property('task_id');",
                  "  });",
                  "  if (j.detail && j.detail.task_id) pm.environment.set('task_id', j.detail.task_id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ask?timeout_seconds=60",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ask"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "timeout_seconds", "value": "60" }
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"goal\": \"Who is the current president of America?\",\n  \"requirements\": [],\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"use_openai\": false\n  }\n}"
            },
            "description": "Implemented in app/api.py. Forces coordinator workflow to skip OpenAI and return a search-derived answer.\n\nThis uses constraints.use_openai=false which is read inside app/celery_worker.py."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /tasks/{{task_id}} (poll task status/result)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('task_id is set', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.environment.get('task_id')).to.be.ok;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}",
            "description": "Implemented in app/api.py. Returns Celery AsyncResult state.\n\nIf ready and successful: includes result.\nIf ready and failed: includes error."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
